text: Francisco Carreón y Marcos (October 5, 1868 – 1939/41) was a Philippine politicians, resistance activist, and member of Katipunan and Republika ng Katagalugan. He was the Vice President of the Philippine revolutionary government from May 6 1902 to July 14 1906.
